import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['u'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'u'?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))
    ax[0].scatter(data['u'], data['diff'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax[0].set_xlabel('u')
    ax[0].set_ylabel('diff')
    ax[0].set_title('diff vs u')
    ax[1].scatter(data['v'], data['diff'], alpha=0.5, color='red')
    ax[1].set_xlabel('v')
    ax[1].set_ylabel('diff')
    ax[1].set_title('diff vs v')
    fig.suptitle("Is there any correlation between 'diff' and 'u' or 'v'?", fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
